<h1
id="lab-define-a-simple-data-structure-using-pydantic-or-dataclasses">Lab:
Define a Simple Data Structure Using Pydantic or Dataclasses</h1>
<h2 id="objectives">Objectives</h2>
<ul>
<li>Understand the difference between Pydantic and dataclasses for
defining data structures.</li>
<li>Learn how to create and validate simple models in Python.</li>
<li>Explore practical use cases for data validation and type
enforcement.</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="real-world-scenario">Real-World Scenario</h2>
<p>Imagine you are building a user registration system for a web
application. You need to ensure that user data such as name, age, and
email are correctly structured and validated before storing them in a
database. Using Pydantic or dataclasses helps you define clear data
models and catch errors early, improving reliability and
maintainability.</p>
<h2 id="step-1-install-pydantic-if-using-pydantic">Step 1: Install
Pydantic (if using Pydantic)</h2>
<div class="sourceCode" id="cb1"><pre
class="sourceCode bash"><code class="sourceCode bash"><span id="cb1-1"><a href="#cb1-1" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="ex">pip</span> install pydantic</span></code></pre></div>
<h2 id="step-2-create-a-data-structure">Step 2: Create a Data
Structure</h2>
<h3 id="using-pydantic">Using Pydantic</h3>
<div class="sourceCode" id="cb2"><pre
class="sourceCode python"><code class="sourceCode python"><span id="cb2-1"><a href="#cb2-1" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="im">from</span> pydantic <span class="im">import</span> BaseModel</span>
<span id="cb2-2"><a href="#cb2-2" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb2-3"><a href="#cb2-3" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="kw">class</span> Person(BaseModel):</span>
<span id="cb2-4"><a href="#cb2-4" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    name: <span class="bu">str</span></span>
<span id="cb2-5"><a href="#cb2-5" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    age: <span class="bu">int</span></span>
<span id="cb2-6"><a href="#cb2-6" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    email: <span class="bu">str</span></span></code></pre></div>
<h3 id="using-dataclasses">Using Dataclasses</h3>
<div class="sourceCode" id="cb3"><pre
class="sourceCode python"><code class="sourceCode python"><span id="cb3-1"><a href="#cb3-1" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="im">from</span> dataclasses <span class="im">import</span> dataclass</span>
<span id="cb3-2"><a href="#cb3-2" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb3-3"><a href="#cb3-3" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="at">@dataclass</span></span>
<span id="cb3-4"><a href="#cb3-4" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="kw">class</span> Person:</span>
<span id="cb3-5"><a href="#cb3-5" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    name: <span class="bu">str</span></span>
<span id="cb3-6"><a href="#cb3-6" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    age: <span class="bu">int</span></span>
<span id="cb3-7"><a href="#cb3-7" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    email: <span class="bu">str</span></span></code></pre></div>
<h2 id="step-3-create-an-instance">Step 3: Create an Instance</h2>
